\subsection{Spectra}
As a result of nucleosynthesis and mixing during SN explosions, iron absorption is commonly seen in SN spectra, either as
\ion{Fe}{2} at low effective temperatures or as \ion{Fe}{3} at higher temperatures. However, neither of these iron features are present in the early-phase
spectra of iPTF13asv. As highlighted in gray regions of Figure \ref{fig:syn++}, spectral feature identification with SYN$++$ \citep{tnm11}
on the iPTF13asv spectrum at $-8.7$ days shows no \ion{Fe}{2} or \ion{Fe}{3}. We also compare the iPTF13asv spectra against both
normal events (Figure \ref{fig:specZoomIn} and super-Chandrasekhar events (Figure \ref{fig:earlySuperC}) to illustrate that, unlike iPTF13asv,
both normal and super-Chandrasekhar SNe have iron absorption features at very early phases. 


